# Concept-graph alias equivalences AND cross-namespace vocabulary bridges
# — Phase 2.2 + Phase 2.5 of the RDF/SHACL enrichment plan
# (plans/rdf-shacl-enrichment-2026-04-26.md).
#
# This file plays TWO complementary roles:
#
#   ROLE 1 (Phase 2.2 — slug-canonicalization aliases). It declares the
#   canonical-form synonyms that previously lived in
#   `lib/ontology/concept_classifier.py::KNOWN_EQUIVALENT_ALIASES`
#   (e.g., `rdfxml` ↔ `rdf-xml`, `jsonld` ↔ `json-ld`, the same-as
#   surface-form family). All such aliases live entirely inside the
#   `ed4all:` namespace at `https://ed4all.io/vocab/` and are walked
#   by the union-find closure in `lib/ontology/aliases.py` to produce
#   a slug → canonical-slug map.
#
#   ROLE 2 (Phase 2.5 — cross-namespace vocabulary bridges). It bridges
#   the parallel terms that exist in both of Ed4All's two production
#   namespaces:
#     * `ed4all:` = `https://ed4all.io/vocab/`  — used by every JSON-LD
#       @context file (concept_graph_semantic, chunk_v4, course,
#       pedagogy_graph). Carries document-shape predicates AND most
#       domain predicates emitted at JSON-LD round-trip time.
#     * `cf:`     = `https://ed4all.dev/ns/courseforge/v1#`  — used by
#       `schemas/context/courseforge_v1.vocabulary.ttl`, the formal
#       RDFS/OWL declaration. Carries the typed classes and the
#       Wave 57+/Phase 2.1 predicate vocabulary with full
#       rdfs:domain / rdfs:range axioms.
#   The two surfaces use the SAME local names for the same intent —
#   `ed4all:Concept` and `cf:Concept` are the same class, just written
#   under different host namespaces by accident of evolution. Phase 2.5
#   formally reconciles them with `owl:equivalentClass` /
#   `owl:equivalentProperty` axioms here so an RDFS/OWL reasoner sees
#   them as the same term and can join data emitted under either
#   namespace without alias gymnastics.
#
# Why owl:equivalentProperty (and owl:equivalentClass), not owl:sameAs?
#   Per LibV2 corpus Q9 (q_20260426_205704_f9dc2230) and Q11
#   (q_20260426_205705_7c3f954f), `owl:sameAs` is reserved for INDIVIDUAL
#   identity — every triple about one individual is entailed about the
#   other in both directions, with full substitution. Using sameAs for
#   either surface-form synonyms or cross-namespace term equivalence
#   would (a) be type-incorrect (these IRIs name CLASSES or PREDICATES,
#   not individuals) and (b) trigger the "sameAs explosion" pitfall
#   under OWL 2 RL reasoning. `owl:equivalentProperty` and
#   `owl:equivalentClass` are the structurally correct vocabularies:
#   they are symmetric, type-respecting (property↔property,
#   class↔class), and bounded in scope. The canonical reference
#   example from the corpus (chunk_00091, HealthIntegrity scenario) is
#   `foaf:name owl:equivalentProperty schema:name` — exactly the
#   pattern used here for `ed4all:bloomLevel ↔ cf:bloomLevel` etc.
#
# Closure semantics:
#   Both `owl:equivalentProperty` and `owl:equivalentClass` are symmetric
#   and transitive (RDF Semantics §11; OWL 2 Direct Semantics). The
#   Python loader builds the equivalence-class closure via union-find
#   so any term in a class canonicalizes to the same representative.
#   For Role-1 aliases the representative is the slug whose IRI carries
#   the `ed4all:isCanonical "true"^^xsd:boolean` annotation; for Role-2
#   bridges the representative is whichever side carries the annotation
#   (currently the `ed4all:` side, since the JSON-LD @context files are
#   the primary emit surface and the bridges are the runtime consumer's
#   path back to the formal cf: vocabulary). If none is annotated, the
#   loader falls back to lexicographic order.
#
# Adding new aliases or bridges:
#   1. For Role 1, mint an `ed4all:<slug>` IRI for the new alias.
#      Declare `<alias> owl:equivalentProperty <existing-canonical>`.
#   2. For Role 2, add `ed4all:<term> owl:equivalentProperty cf:<term>`
#      (or `owl:equivalentClass` for class-typed terms). Both IRIs must
#      already exist — the bridge is purely declarative; we never mint
#      new predicates here.
#   3. Add an `rdfs:label` for the human-readable surface form.
#   4. Add a parity / bridge test entry to
#      `lib/ontology/tests/test_aliases.py`.

@prefix rdf:    <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:   <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix owl:    <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix xsd:    <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix ed4all: <https://ed4all.io/vocab/> .
@prefix cf:     <https://ed4all.dev/ns/courseforge/v1#> .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ontology header
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

<https://ed4all.io/vocab/aliases>
    a owl:Ontology ;
    rdfs:label "Ed4All Concept-Graph Slug Aliases" ;
    rdfs:comment "Canonical slug equivalence classes for the concept-graph extractor. Phase 2.2 — Wave 83." ;
    owl:versionInfo "1.0.0" .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Annotation property — flags the canonical representative of an
# equivalence class so the closure walk can pick a deterministic
# canonical without resorting to lexicographic ordering.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:isCanonical
    a owl:AnnotationProperty ;
    rdfs:label "is canonical" ;
    rdfs:comment "When true on a property IRI in an owl:equivalentProperty class, marks that IRI as the canonical representative for closure-walk resolution." .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 1: RDF/XML serialization format
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:rdf-xml
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "RDF/XML" ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:rdfxml
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "rdfxml" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:rdf-xml .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 2: JSON-LD serialization format
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:json-ld
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "JSON-LD" ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:jsonld
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "jsonld" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:json-ld .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 3: N-Triples serialization format
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:n-triples
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "N-Triples" ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:ntriples
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "ntriples" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:n-triples .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 4: N-Quads serialization format
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:n-quads
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "N-Quads" ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:nquads
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "nquads" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:n-quads .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 5: Turtle serialization format
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:turtle
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Turtle" ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:ttl
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "ttl" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:turtle .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 6: RDF Schema (W3C standard)
# Canonical: the acronym slug `rdfs` matches the W3C namespace prefix
# emitted by `lib/ontology/tech_anchors.py` (Wave 82 Phase C2).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:rdfs
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "RDFS" ;
    rdfs:comment "Canonical slug for the W3C RDF Schema standard." ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:rdf-schema
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "RDF Schema" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:rdfs .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 7: Web Ontology Language (W3C standard)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:owl
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "OWL" ;
    rdfs:comment "Canonical slug for the W3C Web Ontology Language." ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:web-ontology-language
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Web Ontology Language" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:owl .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 8: Shapes Constraint Language (W3C standard)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:shacl
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "SHACL" ;
    rdfs:comment "Canonical slug for the W3C Shapes Constraint Language." ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:shapes-constraint-language
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "Shapes Constraint Language" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:shacl .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Family 9: owl:sameAs surface variants
#
# Per Q11, owl:sameAs is itself the predicate; users in body text
# spell it many ways (`owlsameas`, `owl-sameas`, `sameas`). The slug
# `same-as` is the canonical concept-graph anchor. Note: the equivalence
# below is BETWEEN SURFACE FORMS — it does not assert that any data
# triple uses owl:sameAs as a relation.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:same-as
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "owl:sameAs (surface form)" ;
    rdfs:comment "Canonical concept-graph anchor for the owl:sameAs predicate. Distinct from the predicate itself (http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs)." ;
    ed4all:isCanonical true .

ed4all:owlsameas
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "owlsameas" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:same-as .

ed4all:owl-sameas
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "owl-sameas" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:same-as .

ed4all:sameas
    a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "sameas" ;
    owl:equivalentProperty ed4all:same-as .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 2.5 — Cross-namespace vocabulary bridges.
#
# Bridges between `ed4all:` (https://ed4all.io/vocab/, used by all four
# JSON-LD @context files) and `cf:` (https://ed4all.dev/ns/courseforge/v1#,
# used by the formal RDFS/OWL declaration in
# `schemas/context/courseforge_v1.vocabulary.ttl`). Both surfaces use
# the same local names for the same intent; these axioms make that
# equivalence explicit so reasoners and the union-find closure walker
# treat the two IRIs as a single equivalence class.
#
# Enumeration method: every `cf:<localName>` declared in
# `courseforge_v1.vocabulary.ttl` was checked against every
# `ed4all:<localName>` referenced in the four JSON-LD context files.
# A term appears below ONLY when both surfaces carry the same local
# name with the same intent. Terms unique to one surface (e.g.,
# `cf:CourseModule`, `cf:bloomDistribution`, the chunk-structural
# predicates listed in chunk_v4_v1.jsonld's `_phase2_followup` block)
# are intentionally not bridged — there is no parallel IRI to bridge to.
#
# Class bridges (5).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:Concept owl:equivalentClass cf:Concept .
ed4all:LearningObjective owl:equivalentClass cf:LearningObjective .
ed4all:Misconception owl:equivalentClass cf:Misconception .
ed4all:Chunk owl:equivalentClass cf:Chunk .
ed4all:TargetedConcept owl:equivalentClass cf:TargetedConcept .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Property bridges (13).
#
# Object properties — relations between resources.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

ed4all:bloomLevel owl:equivalentProperty cf:bloomLevel .
ed4all:cognitiveDomain owl:equivalentProperty cf:cognitiveDomain .
ed4all:hierarchyLevel owl:equivalentProperty cf:hierarchyLevel .
ed4all:targetsConcept owl:equivalentProperty cf:targetsConcept .
ed4all:hasMisconception owl:equivalentProperty cf:hasMisconception .
ed4all:hasPrerequisite owl:equivalentProperty cf:hasPrerequisite .
ed4all:isDefinedBy owl:equivalentProperty cf:isDefinedBy .
ed4all:isDerivedFromObjective owl:equivalentProperty cf:isDerivedFromObjective .
ed4all:exemplifiedBy owl:equivalentProperty cf:exemplifiedBy .
ed4all:isMisconceptionOf owl:equivalentProperty cf:isMisconceptionOf .
ed4all:assessesObjective owl:equivalentProperty cf:assessesObjective .

# Datatype properties — literal-valued.

ed4all:bloomVerb owl:equivalentProperty cf:bloomVerb .
ed4all:correction owl:equivalentProperty cf:correction .
